GOV. ROBERT BENTLEY (R),
Alabama: Unfortunately,
I think things like that will
continue. That's

18:51.564 --> 18:57.103 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
why I think it's essential that
we solve this
problem, that we solve it once
and for all.

18:57.136 --> 19:02.475 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: We joined Alabama
Governor
Robert Bentley as he toured
Julia Tutwiler

19:02.508 --> 19:09.915 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Prison, a maximum security
facility for women
outside Montgomery.

19:09.949 --> 19:16.589 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The U.S. Department of Justice
sued Tutwiler
in 2014, citing corruption,
sexual assault

19:16.622 --> 19:22.128 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and harassment of inmates by
staff, just one
of a number of lawsuits accusing
the Alabama

19:22.161 --> 19:25.431 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Corrections System of violating
inmates' rights.

19:25.464 --> 19:30.736 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The violence, the overcrowding
and the federal
measures have pushed the solidly
Republican

19:30.770 --> 19:36.776 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
