the same way
that the first slogan did.

20:19.385 --> 20:24.123 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Among other
things, the new
law, which just went into effect
in January,

20:24.156 --> 20:28.828 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
creates a new class of felonies
for low-level
drug and property crimes that
keeps offenders

20:28.861 --> 20:31.397 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
out of state prisons.

20:31.430 --> 20:36.335 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Alabama was the only state that
considered
all forms of property theft
violent crimes.

20:36.368 --> 20:42.208 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
It's now reclassified
third-degree burglary
as a nonviolent crime. The law
requires the

20:42.241 --> 20:48.147 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
hiring of 100 additional
probation and parole
officers. It mandates that
parole boards create

20:48.180 --> 20:53.953 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
