supposed to be
complying with.

21:21.914 --> 21:23.883 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
We didn't do that. This
legislation did.

21:23.916 --> 21:30.022 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Are you making
this push for
budgetary reasons, or for moral
reasons?

21:30.055 --> 21:34.560 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CAM WARD: Interestingly enough,
it depends
on who you ask who -- why they
support it.

21:34.593 --> 21:36.462 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You have some who say, hey, for
budgetary
purposes.

21:36.495 --> 21:38.197 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: We just have to
do this.

21:38.230 --> 21:40.499 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CAM WARD: This is the second
largest item
in our budget. We have got to do
something

21:40.533 --> 21:42.334 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
about it.

21:42.368 --> 21:44.770 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Then you have those for moral
purposes. I
would say many of my Democrat
colleagues would

21:44.803 --> 21:49.508 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
say it's a moral issue for them.
