men who had recently been
released from prison

22:52.871 --> 22:54.506 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
about the conditions.

22:54.540 --> 22:57.443 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAN: It's harder to keep clean
when you got
all the people in there like
that.

22:57.476 --> 22:59.245 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Did you have
that, Dwight?
Was it crowded?

22:59.278 --> 23:01.180 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DWIGHT HAGOOD, Former Inmate:
Yes, sir. About
every day, there was a stabbing,
fighting,

23:01.213 --> 23:02.348 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
cutting.

23:02.381 --> 23:06.852 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Every day, you
saw things like
that?

23:06.885 --> 23:09.088 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
DWIGHT HAGOOD: Every day.

23:09.121 --> 23:13.559 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: These men are now
receiving
help from Pastor Kenneth
Glasgow...

23:13.592 --> 23:18.264 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
KENNETH GLASGOW, Pastor,
Ordinary People Society:
I'm just now hitting 15 years,
after doing

23:18.297 --> 23:19.932 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
14 years.

23:19.965 --> 23:22.568 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BROWN: ... who, after serving 14
years on
a drug charge, created the
Ordinary People

23:22.601 --> 23:29.975 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Society, an organization and
halfway house
to help people transition out of
prison.

23:30.009 --> 23:36.815 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Glasgow applauds the efforts
made by the legislature
so far, but is also calling for
a more fundamental

23:36.849 --> 23:39.618 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
change to the way people view
inmates.

23:39.652 --> 23:44.990 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KENNETH GLASGOW: We're not
ex-convicts. We're
not ex-offenders. We're not
ex-felons. Don't

23:45.024 --> 23:52.598 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
classify us. We are people with
felony convictions,
people that have paid their debt
to society.

23:52.631 --> 23:54.400 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
People. People.

23:54.433 --> 24:00.205 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BRYAN STEVENSON: Look, it's
still legal in
this state to impose a mandatory
life without

24:00.239 --> 24:06.312 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
parole sentence on someone in
simple possession
of 2.5 pounds of marijuana,
using it for their

24:06.345 --> 24:08.147 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
personal use.

24:08.180 --> 24:13.152 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I'm representing a man who's a
75-year-old
disabled combat veteran who was
found to have

24:13.185 --> 24:18.190 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
2.5 pounds of pot, because he
was using it
to deal with stents in his
heart. And because

24:18.223 --> 24:24.630 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
