series, Inside
Kenya.

27:22.140 --> 27:27.446 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The East African nation is the
United States'
primary ally in the region, and
in the fight

27:27.479 --> 27:33.719 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
against the deadly terror group
Al-Shabaab,
based in Somalia. Al-Shabaab
attacks government

27:33.752 --> 27:39.358 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and military institutions in
Somalia, but
it has also launched major
attacks in neighboring

27:39.391 --> 27:41.226 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Kenya.

27:41.260 --> 27:46.064 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Special correspondent Nick
Schifrin and producer
Zach Fannin traveled extensively
throughout

27:46.098 --> 27:49.301 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Northeastern Kenya, along the
Somali border.

27:49.334 --> 27:55.007 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Tonight, with the help of the
Pulitzer Center
on Crisis Reporting, we start
our series with

27:55.040 --> 28:00.178 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
