associated
with al-Qaida, and you know what
al-Qaidas

28:24.937 --> 28:26.705 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
are.

28:26.738 --> 28:29.775 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NICK SCHIFRIN: Officer Julius
Kiragu heads
Kenya's administrative police in
Wajir, only

28:29.808 --> 28:34.680 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
70 miles from the Somali border.
Every night,
they search for smuggled weapons
and hiding

28:34.713 --> 28:36.515 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
fighters.

28:36.548 --> 28:42.187 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JULIUS KIRAGU: They pretend they
are selling
milk and all these things, but
they are waiting

28:42.220 --> 28:44.156 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
for the appropriate time to
strike.

28:44.189 --> 28:49.795 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NICK SCHIFRIN: Most of his
officers are ethnic
Somali, like the majority of the
local population.

28:49.828 --> 28:55.601 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Some officers wear civilian
clothing and ride
around in unmarked cars. They
work with local

28:55.634 --> 28:58.236 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
tribal chiefs, like Zein
Abdulla.

28:58.270 --> 29:00.038 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
What kinds of weapons have you
found here?

29:00.072 --> 29:03.642 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ZEIN ABDULLA, Tribal Chief:
There were guns.
There were grenades. There were
ammunitions

29:03.675 --> 29:04.810 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and such things.

29:04.843 --> 29:07.179 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
NICK SCHIFRIN: So, Shabaab has
supporters
even here?

29:07.212 --> 29:11.516 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ZEIN ABDULLA: So, they have
representatives
at least in every district.

29:11.550 --> 29:19.524 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NICK SCHIFRIN: Al-Shabaab has
waged a decade-long
war in Somalia. In 2011, Kenya
invaded Somalia,

29:19.558 --> 29:22.561 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in a campaign called Protect the
Country.

29:22.594 --> 29:25.464 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Emmanuel Chirchir was the face
of the campaign
in Somalia, and on Twitter.

29:25.497 --> 29:28.767 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
EMMANUEL CHIRCHIR, Kenya Army:
This gives
an opportunity to tell the rest
of the world

29:28.800 --> 29:32.237 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
what is true and what is
happening in the
battle space.

29:32.270 --> 29:37.242 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NICK SCHIFRIN: At first, Kenyan
and other
African troops pushed Shabaab
out of its strongholds,

29:37.275 --> 29:45.217 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and raised the Somali flag. But
after an operational
pause, Shabaab is strengthening.

29:45.250 --> 29:53.325 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In January, Shabaab fighters
took over a Kenyan
base. It was Kenya's worst ever
military disaster.

29:53.358 --> 29:59.898 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
More than 100 soldiers died,
including Chirchir's
brother.

29:59.931 --> 30:07.439 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
EMMANUEL CHIRCHIR: My brother
died immediately,
instantly. This is what he loved
most. I am

30:07.472 --> 30:13.512 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
happy that he actually died
doing what he
loved most.

30:13.545 --> 30:18.750 align:left position:25%,start line:66.67% size:75%
NICK SCHIFRIN:
Twenty-nine-year-old Dan
Chirchir
had only been in Somalia for
three weeks.

30:18.784 --> 30:25.490 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
His funeral, with full military
honors, was
held at the family's estate in
Western Kenya.

30:25.524 --> 30:30.762 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The explosion that killed him
was unprecedented.
Al-Shabaab got inside the El
Adde base to

30:30.796 --> 30:32.798 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
detonate a car bomb, or VBIED.

30:32.831 --> 30:37.369 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
EMMANUEL CHIRCHIR: The
penetration of that
VBIED changed the game.

30:37.402 --> 30:39.805 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
NICK SCHIFRIN: What can you tell
me about
the El Adde attack?

30:39.838 --> 30:44.576 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAN (through translator): The
attack was carried
out by one of our brigades. They
were trained

30:44.609 --> 30:46.378 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
commandos.

30:46.411 --> 30:49.881 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NICK SCHIFRIN: This 40-year-old
Somali says
he's a member of Al-Shabaab. He
says the El

30:49.915 --> 30:54.186 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Adde attack took eight months to
plan. He
threatened to kill me if we
didn't keep him

30:54.219 --> 30:55.721 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
anonymous.

30:55.754 --> 31:00.325 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What's the main motivation for
you and your
men to have joined Al-Shabaab?

31:00.358 --> 31:05.363 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAN (through translator): I
joined thee group
to get a job. Somalia is a place
where there

31:05.397 --> 31:07.199 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
